==English==

===Etymology===
From Greek [[Ἰνδία]], via Latin '''India''', derived from Ἰνδός, the '''[[Indus]]''' River. Ἰνδός itself comes from the {{Pers.}}  + {{Gr.}} φοβοσ=''fear''

===Noun===
'''Indophobia'''

# Negative attitudes expressed by some [[British]] Indologists against [[Indian]] history, society, religions, culture and [[South Asia]] in general, also used to describe specific prejudice against people of [[India]].